			<notes/>
			<notesNormalized/>
			<notesHtml/>
			<text>Interventions for infected necrosis 
Infected pancreatic necrosis with failed conservative treatment
Traditional open surgical approaches
Minimally invasive techniques
1. Endoscopic drainage +/- Endoscopic Necrosectomy5
2. Multiple transluminal gateway technique6
Minimally invasive surgery:
1. Video assisted retroperitoneal debridement
2. Laparoscopic debridement
Percutaneous drainage: Cannot clear solid debris; problem of fistulas; surgical rescue rates of 53-62%.3
1. Fernandez. Ann Surg 1998; 2. Rau. Surgery 2005; 3. Bradley. J Gastrointest Surg 2008; 4. Gluck . Clin Gastroenterol Hepatol 2010; 5. Seewald. GIE 2005; 6. Varadarajulu GIE 2011
Mortality rates: 11% - 27%1, 2
Combined modality treatment: (1) Transgastric stenting + (2) Percutaneous or NC irrigation and drainage4</text>
		</slide>
