			<notes/>
			<notesNormalized/>
			<notesHtml/>
			<text>Criteria for direct endoscopic necrosectomy
Eligibility 
Infected necrosis. 
Duration of fluid collection greater than 4 weeks.
Well-formed wall surrounding the collection.
Collection accessible endoscopically.
Located within 1 cm of the gastric wall.

Contraindications 
Coagulopathy that cannot be corrected.
Endoscopically inaccessible sites.
Sterile necrosis.
Predominantly solid necrosis with minimal liquefaction.

</text>
		</slide>
