			<notesHtml/>
			<text>Technical notes
Initial EUS-guided acess of WON
Therapeutic linear echoendoscope 
19G needle; Guide-wires (0.025 – 0.035”)
Puncture tract dilators: co-axial, balloon, cautery devices
Drainage and maintaining access
Double pig-tail plastic stents (PS) OR
Customized large diameter SEMS
Faciliate repeat entry into WON
May decrease need for intervention
Endoscopic necrosectomy if lack of response
Gastroscope with CO2 insufflation
Large diameter balloon dilatation for access if PS used
Accessories eg basket, retrieval net</text>
